main event: A housewife observed a lighted object hovering over a field in Dewey, Kansas, for 10 to 15 minutes on July 14, 1959.
interesting points: The object suddenly disappeared after hovering for a while., The witness felt concerned and asked a neighbor, who did not see the object., The object was reported to have no identifiable characteristics., Another sighting was reported in Tulsa, Oklahoma, on September 15, 1960., The Tulsa object changed shape from elliptical to circular and emitted a bright reddish-orange light.
sighted object: lighted object hovering in the sky
